-rotating core. A diverse\nassembly history consisting of multiple gas-poor mergers of a variety of\nprogenitor mass ratios and orbits is likely to be needed to account for the\npredominance of low spins and the wide range of central and main-body velocity\nfeatures reported here for local massive ETGs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Jan 2020 19:01:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-11"}
