e values reported in the\nliterature and in line with similarly luminous dSphs; this is consistent with\nTucana not being an exception to the too-big-to-fail problem, nor living in a\ndark matter halo much more massive than those of its siblings. As for the\nmetallicity properties, we do not find anything unusual; there are hints of the\npresence of a [Fe/H] gradient but more data are needed to pin its presence\ndown.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Jan 2020 15:43:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-01"}
